text.tspan: Shopping and Research in Ardenhaven
The party completed their shopping in Ardenfords local shops, acquiring items
including a discounted Sleep scroll and replacement throwing axes. Marwen
stole an uncatalogued holy book during her research at the Concordance
Library, successfully evading detection.
16 Arethum, Afternoon
Confrontation with Giant Spider
The party stealthily approached a web-covered camp, negotiated with a giant
spider, and killed a hatching spiderling. After stabilizing a worker, they
destroyed the spider eggs, and prepared to return to Ardenford for payment.
16 Arethum, Midday
Consultation with Elarion the Elf
Marwen approached Elarion, the elf librarian, to seek guidance on ruins, dwarf
guides, and local shops. With valuable directions and recommendations
received, the party concluded their conversation and prepared to continue their
errands.
16 Arethum, Morning
Tavern Brawl with Imperium Traders
After a late-night bonding session, the party faced escalating tensions with
Imperium traders. Bazgar initiated a brawl, knocking out several traders before
Thorgrim enforced peace with free beer, allowing the party to rest undisturbed.
15 Arethum, Night
Goblin Raid Resolution
The party defeated the goblin ambush, with Marwen incinerating several foes
and Sabriel providing healing. They spared one goblin who fled, then returned
to the farmer to receive payment and bonus cheese for the rescued sheep,
concluding the job.
15 Arethum, Afternoon
Resting Corwin Caldor
The party fought off skeletons, identified Renns grandfather, Corwin Caldor,
and successfully returned his intact remains to the watchtower. After burying
him, they received payment from Renn before seeking further work.
15 Arethum, Midday
The Compass Edge Forms
Bazgar, Sabriel, and Marwen first met at the Wayward Compass in Ardenford,
traded names and first impressions, and agreed to take their first contract
together.
15 Arethum, Morning
